🛡️ Advanced Web Application Security Testing using OWASP ZAP

📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates advanced web application vulnerability assessment using OWASP ZAP. The tool is used to identify security weaknesses in web applications by intercepting HTTP traffic, analyzing requests and responses, and simulating real-world attack scenarios.

The project focuses on both automated and manual testing approaches to understand vulnerabilities at a deeper level.

🎯 Objectives

Identify vulnerabilities in web applications
Understand HTTP request and response structure
Perform automated and manual security testing
Analyze vulnerability severity and impact
Provide remediation strategies

🧠 Concept

Web applications communicate using HTTP/HTTPS protocols. OWASP ZAP acts as a proxy between the browser and server, allowing interception and analysis of this communication.

The tool performs
Spidering to discover application structure
Passive scanning to analyze responses
Active scanning to simulate attacks

⚙️ Tools and Technologies Used

Kali Linux (VMware Environment)
OWASP ZAP
Web Browser (Firefox)
Test Target Application (OWASP Juice Shop or demo web apps)

🏗️ Working Architecture

Browser
↓
ZAP Proxy
↓
Web Server

ZAP intercepts and analyzes all traffic between client and server.

🚀 Implementation Steps

🔹 1. Installation and Setup

Installed OWASP ZAP using Kali package manager

Command used
sudo apt update
sudo apt install zaproxy -y

Launched using
zaproxy

🔹 2. Session Initialization

Selected persistent session to store scan data and results

🔹 3. Target Selection

Used a safe and vulnerable test application
[http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) (OWASP Juice Shop)
or
[http://demo.testfire.net](http://demo.testfire.net)

🔹 4. Automated Scan

Used Quick Start Automated Scan feature
Entered target URL
Started scan using Attack option

🔹 5. Manual Testing

Enabled intercept mode to capture HTTP requests
Analyzed request and response structure
Forwarded traffic to observe behavior

🔹 6. Spidering

Discovered all application endpoints and pages

🔹 7. Active Scan

Simulated attack payloads to detect vulnerabilities

🔹 8. Results Analysis

Viewed alerts categorized by severity
Analyzed vulnerability details and solutions

